The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Governor Gopalkrishna Gandhi took a lift in a police Gypsy in his convoy after his car developed a snag on Red Road on the way to Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Gol Park, around 5pm on Thursday. The governor returned to Raj Bhavan in a spare car that was sent to the institute.     A 28-year-old IT employee, Soumen Kundu, was injured after being knocked down by a bus plying on route 201 (WB25 3268) near Baisakhi crossing in Salt Lake. Police said the motorcycle skidded and nearly came under the front wheels of the bus. Jharna Das, who saw the mishap, said two buses on the same route were racing and a motorcycle was caught in between them before being hit by one. The bus was impounded but the driver managed to flee. Kundu was taken to ILS Multispeciality Clinic in Salt Lake. His condition was stable.     Manti Singh and Balaram Das were injured when a Matador knocked them down on Harish Mukherjee Road early on Thursday. Police said the incident took place around 5.45am when the two were crossing the road. They were taken to SSKM Hospital. The driver fled with the vehicle.    A motorcycle was stolen from Ekbalpore Lane on Wednesday night. A complaint has been lodged by owner Khondekarul Islam.    A group of SUCI supporters demonstrated in front of the north gate of Raj Bhavan on Thursday afternoon demanding reduction in bus and taxi fares and the price of LPG cylinders. Eight people were arrested. Supporters of BJPs minority cell assembled near No. 4 bridge protesting the sale of hooch.    A Tata Sumo, a Maruti Omni and a Tata Indica stolen from the city in 2007 were recovered from different parts of Malda recently. A man was arrested in this connection.                                                                                                                                                                   
